http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Thiruvananthapuram/Clinical-skill-lab-to-be-set-up/article14009994.ece

The first clinical skill lab in the State which uses simulators to train doctors and nurses in delivering maternal and child care in various clinical situations will be set up at the Kerala State Institute for Health and Family Welfare here, Health Minister V.S. Sivakumar has said.He was inaugurating the hostel facility constructed on the institute premises at Rs.6.5 crore for conducting residential training for the officials of Health Service here on Tuesday.The skill lab was in the process of being set up. Similar skill labs would be set up in Ernakulam and Kozhikode also. The manner in which the staff who were trained in the skill lab were delivering maternal and child care in hospitals would be monitored and reviewedAll facilities for rendering timely training for all Health Service employees have been arranged at the institute, where about 4,000-odd officials of the health sector receives in-service training every year. Apart from the training programmes conducted by the Health Department and the National Health Mission, training by external agencies such as the UNICEF, WHO and UNDP are also conducted at the institute.